petition is there, but the choice is there for them as to whether or not they want to open their shops.</p><p class="a">Similarly, with this bill they are given the choice, and the local body has got a choice of whether they want to ask the people or not, like in Rotorua, where the demand is—because Taupō is open on Easter Sunday whereas Rotorua is not. People are at a disadvantage. The businesses feel the pinch, and that choice is being given in this bill. I hope that with this bill, when it goes through, a lot of businesses will appreciate what this Government has done. Thank you.</p></div></body>
